fields: fleet , schema , labels , and retention_policy . DELETE /devices/{deviceId} De-provision a device. Streams owned by the device are flushed and closed; historical readings are retained per the active retention policy. POST /devices/{deviceId}/ping DEPRECATED Sends a synchronous health probe to the device. Removed in v3.0 — heartbeat data is now pushed via the bidirectional /streams/{id}/control channel. Migrate by subscribing to device.heartbeat events. /streams · Telemetry streams Streams are append-only sequences of typed sensor readings. Each device may own one or more streams keyed by schema. Streams support batched ingestion and server-side aggregation windows. GET /streams List streams visible to the caller. Filter by device_id , schema , or state=open|closed . POST /streams Open a new stream bound to a device and a registered schema. Returns a stream_id and a write-token valid for 24 hours. POST /streams/{id}/readings Append a batch of readings. Payloads are validated against the stream's schema; rows that fail validation are rejected individually and reported in the response. Rust let batch = vec![
    Reading::new( "core_temp" , 42.7 ),
    Reading::new( "core_temp" , 42.9 ),
];
client.streams().push( "str_8f2a" , &batch). await ?; GET /streams/{id}/tail DEPRECATED Long-poll the tail of a stream. Removed in v3.0 — replaced by the WebSocket subscription endpoint at wss://gw.ferroflux.io/v2/streams/{id}/subscribe . DELETE /streams/{id} Close a stream and seal its log segment. Closed streams remain queryable but reject further writes. /alerts · Alerts & rules Server-side rule engine that produces alerts from stream data. Rules are declared in .flux configuration and evaluated against sliding windows. GET /alerts List open alerts. Filter by severity , rule_id , or device_id . POST /alerts/{id}/acknowledge Acknowledge an alert, recording the operator identity and an optional note. Acknowledged alerts remain visible but are excluded from the on-call paging queue. GET /alerts/rules Enumerate active alerting rules with their evaluation status and last-fired timestamp. POST /alerts/{id}/snooze DEPRECATED Temporarily suppress an alert. Removed in v3.0 — use rule-level inhibitions configured in retention.flux . The legacy endpoint silently no-ops for snoozes longer than 1 hour. /auth · Authentication Token issuance, rotation, and revocation. Auth endpoints are not tenant-scoped and accept client credentials directly. POST /auth/token Exchange a client ID and secret for a short-lived bearer token (default TTL: 3600s). JSON { "grant_type" : "client_credentials" , "client_id" : "ff_cl_a91f..." , "client_secret" : "***" , "scope" : "streams:write devices:read" } POST /auth/revoke Revoke a token immediately. Useful when a device is suspected of compromise; pair with DELETE /devices/{id} to fully de-provision. POST /auth/keys/rotate Rotate the tenant's signing keys. New tokens are signed with the fresh key immediately; the prior key remains valid for verification for 24 hours to allow rolling restarts. Warning: Rotation invalidates all cached JWKS at downstream services. Schedule during a low-traffic maintenance window. On This Page Overview Auth header /de